Here is the commit message:
NIFI-4869 Added SAX utility method for SplitXML processor.
 Added unit tests. Added test resources to RAT exclude list. This closes #2466

Here is the root cause:
The bug was likely caused by the potential for XML External Entity (XXE) attacks due to the use of a SAX parser without proper configuration to disable external entity processing and DOCTYPE declarations. This could allow malicious XML content to be processed, leading to security vulnerabilities.

